## Browser fallback

If `WebFetch` returns a login page, SSO prompt, or auth error, immediately
use `cursor-ide-browser` (`browser_navigate` + `browser_snapshot`) instead.
Do not troubleshoot the fetch or try other MCP servers first.

- For JIRA/Confluence data, use `user-atlassian-mcp-server` or
  `user-nike-dev-integration-system-mcp` instead of the browser.

## SSO-protected pages

When a URL requires SSO/corporate authentication:

1. Open it in the IDE browser with `position: "beside"` so the user can
   see the page and sign in themselves.
2. Do NOT attempt to automate the SSO login flow -- the user must
   complete it interactively.
3. Do NOT fall back to `open` (system browser) -- the user needs the
   page in the IDE browser so the agent can interact with it afterward.
4. Tell the user the browser panel is open and ask them to sign in.
5. Once the user confirms they are authenticated, use `browser_snapshot`
   to read the page and continue.
6. If the direct URL fails to load or gets stuck after SSO, navigate to
   the Okta home page (`https://nike.okta.com`) first so the user can
   sign in there, then navigate back to the original URL.
